<br>
I'm honestly trying to remember the last time I went to one and DIDN'T get my order jacked up. <br>
<br>
Last time I went this lady in front of me asked for a Milk Shake for her kids. THe girl said the machine was empty with the implication that No, you can't have a shake. Not broken mind you.. just empty. So the lady asked...<br>
<br>
&quot;Well is anyone planning on refilling it?&quot;<br>
<br>
The girl had to think about it for a while. <br>
<br>
&quot;Uhh... I guess, but I dunno how to do it.&quot;<br>
<br>
She calls another kid for help. He fills it. Sad thing is it wasn't difficult at all. Grab the bag of shake stuff they have. Take the top off the shake machine. Pour the shakey stuff in. Put top back on and hit the shake machine switch. Obviously a machine designed to make life easy for the employees.... apparently they may need to look at some re-engineering.<br>
<br>
I thought, well maybe she has never been shown how to do it. Which I found difficult to believe since she was in front... a cashier... she knew where everything else was. I gave her the benefit of the doubt -- until it was my turn to order.<br>
<br>
I ordered. When I was done the final tab was $4.89. She proceeds to tell me... and I kid you not....<br>
<br>
&quot;That will be four dollars and....uhh... whatever that says.&quot;<br>
<br>
I've been ordering my food at fast food places ever since I was a 13-15 years old. And thats the first time I have had the cashier not know that .89 is eighty-nine cents. <br>
<br>
Maybe I'm just getting old and becoming a fuddy-duddy, but I just don't remember encountering this many clueless workers say 5+ years ago.  <br>
